			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<strong>Deeplocal was just named the 2012 Overall and Small Business Best Place to Work in Pittsburgh by the Pittsburgh Business Times</strong></p>
<p>
	<strong>Deeplocal was named Small Agency of the Year in the Northeast. We are an innovation studio that is most known for our work in advertising.</strong></p>
<p>
	<strong>Deeplocal is looking for great software engineering interns to join our team of creative engineers in summer 2013 and spring 2013.</strong> This position will require a person that is passionate about learning new skills and comfortable with challenges. This person must truly be comfortable managing their own time and maintaining multiple projects. Deeplocal&rsquo;s internship program goal is to find future full-time employees.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Qualities and Skills we are looking for:</strong><br />
	- Experience in coding (language-agnostic)<br />
	- Passion for good design<br />
	- Driven and self-motivated<br />
	- Hard worker<br />
	- Knowledge of Object-Oriented Programming techniques to create interactive media<br />
	- Examples of independent and group work<br />
	<br />
	<strong>What type of engineering intern are you looking for?</strong><br />
	We are looking for an engineer that can do web programming but has a computer science background. Our engineers work with microcontrollers, low level programming, server side and client side web programming, etc. We need an engineer that is smart, not stuck in one language or one environment, and not scared to learn new things. You will join a team of great people who will help you learn. While electronics and mechanical backgrounds are great they are not the driving force behind this job. If you don&#39;t come from a CS background we just need to see solid examples of work that shoes you have a CS understanding. A passion for design helps as well.</p>
<p>
	<strong>What is Deeplocal?</strong><br />
	Deeplocal is a design and development studio based in Pittsburgh, PA with a satellite office in Venice, CA. Deeplocal is most known for its ability to manufacture highly functioning and often intricate, online and offline experiences in short amounts of time. While the company is relatively small, the team collaborates closely internally and with our clients. The small size and limited overhead management allows us to focus on getting things done quickly and rapidly iterating.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Deeplocal internal skill set is widely varied and includes a high level of proven competency in many areas including:</strong><br />
	Software Engineering (web, mobile, low-level, etc)<br />
	UI / UX and Interaction Design<br />
	Visual Design and Illustration<br />
	Electronics Engineering / Circuit Design and Build<br />
	Fabrication in Plastics, Metal, and Wood</p>
<p>
	Deeplocal has worked for our clients in the fields of visual design, mobile application design and development, product design, and future visioning. <strong>Our direct client list includes: Google, Toyota Motor Sales, DirectTV, Turner Broadcast Systems, MillerCoors, Air France, Volkswagen, GOOD Magazine, Reebok, American Eagle Outfitters, PNC Bank, Gap, Nike, and many others.&nbsp;</strong></p>
